    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but it feels like you're saying humanitarian duty doesn't actually matter if a democracy doesn't pop up immediately after. if we just sit by and watch massacres happen because \"state building\" is too hard, isn't that a failure of morality? isnt there a middle ground between \"total success\" and \"total failure\" where we just focus on saving lives?",
